The Dirty Pipe vulnerability (CVE-2018-5754) allowed a non-root user to escalate their privileges by manipulating file descriptors in a way that bypassed permission checks. The vulnerability was fixed in the Linux kernel, so attempting to exploit it would be futile on patched systems. However, understanding the concept can help in developing better security measures.

